First known as a single person and now recognized as a collective (a quartet as of 2019), the band's members remain anonymous, their faces obscured by black hoods in all photos.
Hailed as some of the most exciting music coming out of New York by NME in 2018, Blood Cultures' genre-bending sound is often characterized as psychedelic pop, electropop, and chillwave.
Blood Cultures released their first album, Happy Birthday, in 2017.
A Universe Despairs, in September 2019.
Their third record, LUNO, was released on May 28, 2021.
